	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 87-11 17 (63)"/>
			<p>I have the honor to present below some informative material on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351"
					type="subject">Jewish question</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html"
					>Bulgaria</placeName> including an article from the <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1069" type="subject">newspaper</term>
				<orgName ref="#ehri_dr_dnes">DNES</orgName> of <date when="1943-03-22">March 22, 1943</date>, and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-843" type="subject">letter</term> from a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> graduate of the <orgName ref="#_2"
					>American College</orgName> of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>. [â€¦]</p>
			<p>The most cursory reading of the article shows that it was written for the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-330" type="subject">purpose of stirring up feeling</term> against <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> as a class. The most definite charge is
				that of hoarding. It is well known that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject"
					>Jews</term> were long ago placed under the most rigid <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-658"
					type="subject">restrictions</term> with regard to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">food</term>. Further, they have been so thoroughly <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">robbed of all their possessions</term>, including all
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-931" type="subject">bank accounts</term>, that few of them have any
				considerable <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-888" type="subject">wealth</term> now at their disposal.
				The general terms employed by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-799" type="subject">writer</term>
				would indicate that he is not writing on a factual basis but in order to produce an effect, that is, suspicion and hatred toward the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jew</term>.</p>
			<p>This is the first <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-357" type="subject">inflammatory article</term> against
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> which has appeared in any <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1069" type="subject">newspaper</term> for a long period. All evidence
				coming our [sic] of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName> indicates that the
					<term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207?page=1" type="subject">people</term> generally disapprove of the
				harsh <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">measures</term> being taken by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004295" type="subject">Government</term> against <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and do what they can to alleviate their
				condition. The recent <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-984" type="subject">protests</term> by many
				leading citizens and by more than forty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1004" type="subject">members of
					Parliament</term> are sufficient evidence of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-813" type="subject"
					>attitude</term> of <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_bulgarians">Bulgarians</term> toward the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">anti-Jewish measures</term> inaugurated by the
					<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000117">Filov</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term>.</p>
